{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NkAmpZ1Dbwzi8UkJsHYz6P","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The spec is minimal — no explicit field names are defined for the user model. I'll use conventional CRUD fields (`id`, `name`, `email`) and standard HTTP status codes (201 for POST, 200 for GET/PUT, 204 for DELETE).\n\n**Decomposition:** Three components:\n1. **store** — thread-safe in-memory map storing User records, exposing Create/Get/Update/Delete operations. Atomic.\n2. **handlers** — HTTP handlers for the 4 CRUD endpoints, wired to the store. Atomic.\n3. **integrate-user-service** — `main.go` wiring store + handlers + router, listening on :8080. Atomic.\n\nComposite source dir: `internal/userservice/` (common parent of `internal/userservice/store` and `internal/userservice/handlers`). Writing `README.md` and `theory-of-operation.md` there now."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":348,"cache_read_input_tokens":20287,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":348},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ff89870-3398-4b2d-8b7c-3e366138ecf4","uuid":"fae21c9f-c6ce-4ee3-8bfa-f0fd25f9dcc3"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01NkAmpZ1Dbwzi8UkJsHYz6P","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_012xWByGihk4VLVXt6HfPeMc","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/user-service/output/internal/userservice/README.md","content":"# userservice\n\nPurpose: Provides an in-memory HTTP user management service with CRUD operations over a REST API.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\nA self-contained package implementing create, read, update, and delete operations for user records. It exposes an HTTP server on port 8080 with JSON request and response bodies.\n\n## Components\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| [store](store/README.md) | Thread-safe in-memory store for User records |\n| [handlers](handlers/README.md) | HTTP CRUD handlers wired to the store |\n\nSee [theory-of-operation.md](theory-of-operation.md) for data-flow details.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":348,"cache_read_input_tokens":20287,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":348},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ff89870-3398-4b2d-8b7c-3e366138ecf4","uuid":"e3d079f3-335f-4c3e-8e94-f6f03aaa0e35"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012xWByGihk4VLVXt6HfPeMc","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/user-service/output/internal/userservice/README.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ff89870-3398-4b2d-8b7c-3e366138ecf4","uuid":"395a1eb6-4a58-42d1-8ce1-2b2f9388edcc","timestamp":"2026-04-05T08:15:08.515Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/user-service/output/internal/userservice/README.md","content":"# userservice\n\nPurpose: Provides an in-memory HTTP user management service with CRUD operations over a REST API.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\nA self-contained package implementing create, read, update, and delete operations for user records. It exposes an HTTP server on port 8080 with JSON request and response bodies.\n\n## Components\n\n| Component | Description |\n|-----------|-------------|\n| [store](store/README.md) | Thread-safe in-memory store for User records |\n| [handlers](handlers/README.md) | HTTP CRUD handlers wired to the store |\n\nSee [theory-of-operation.md](theory-of-operation.md) for data-flow details.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_014oQkYQcpXwvpLvgFJhnsKk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011ws5QzYHQzfASLKaMgNNux","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/david/Go/src/github.com/cornjacket/ai-builder/acceptance-spec/sandbox/regressions/user-service/output/internal/userservice/theory-of-operation.md","content":"# Theory of Operation\n\nPurpose: Describes the data flow between the store and handlers components within the userservice package.\n\nTags: architecture, design\n\n## Data Flow\n\nAn incoming HTTP request is routed by the server mux in `main.go` to the appropriate handler in the `handlers` package. Each handler parses the request, calls the corresponding method on the `store`, and writes a JSON response.\n\n```\nHTTP Client\n    |\n    v\n+---------------------------+\n|  main.go (net/http mux)   |\n|  :8080                    |\n+---------------------------+\n    |\n    | routes request to\n    v\n+---------------------------+\n|  handlers package         |\n|  CreateUser               |\n|  GetUser                  |\n|  UpdateUser               |\n|  DeleteUser               |\n+---------------------------+\n    |\n    | calls\n    v\n+---------------------------+\n|  store package            |\n|  in-memory map[string]User|\n|  protected by sync.RWMutex|\n+---------------------------+\n```\n\n## Request Lifecycle\n\n```\nRequest arrives\n    |\n    +-- POST /users ---------> handlers.CreateUser\n    |                              |-> store.Create(user) -> assigns UUID -> returns User\n    |                              |<- 201 JSON User\n    |\n    +-- GET /users/{id} -----> handlers.GetUser\n    |                              |-> store.Get(id) -> returns (User, bool)\n    |                              |<- 200 JSON User   (found)\n    |                              |<- 404             (not found)\n    |\n    +-- PUT /users/{id} -----> handlers.UpdateUser\n    |                              |-> store.Update(id, user) -> returns (User, bool)\n    |                              |<- 200 JSON User   (found)\n    |                              |<- 404             (not found)\n    |\n    +-- DELETE /users/{id} --> handlers.DeleteUser\n                                   |-> store.Delete(id) -> returns bool\n                                   |<- 204             (found)\n                                   |<- 404             (not found)\n```\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1402,"cache_read_input_tokens":20635,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1402},"output_tokens":72,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5ff89870-3398-4b2d-8b7c-3e366138ecf4","uuid":"853859d5-a0c0-42aa-82b6-50f39f2c50de"}
